# Docs Sync Required

- Documentation is part of the implementation, not a follow-up task.
- When adding or changing MDX pages, update frontmatter and run `pnpm run docs:links`.
- When site config, plugins, or routing behavior changes, update `CLAUDE.md` and `README.md` if commands or deploy flow
  shift.
- Public engine docs under `content/docs/**` are generated from `blit386/docs/` by `scripts/sync-docs-from-engine.mjs`.
  Never hand-edit a generated page: edit the canonical source in the engine repo and run `pnpm run sync:docs`. Which
  docs publish (and their URL, sidebar order, and subtitle) live in the engine repo's `blit386/docs/_sitemap.json`
  manifest, not in this repo's script; add, remove, or reorder a published page by editing that manifest, then run
  `pnpm run sync:docs`. Pages omitted from the manifest stay link-only on GitHub. See `CLAUDE.md` (Documentation
  mirror).
- When `pnpm run` scripts or preflight steps change, update `.claude/skills/*/SKILL.md` and affected
  `.cursor/rules/*.mdc`.
- If no docs update is needed, state why explicitly in the final response.
